(1, '<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Приемат се за публикуване следните категории публикации: научна статия, обзор, научно съобщение и съобщения за конференции и симпозиуми. Работите се публикуват на български или на английски език.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Ръкописит</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">e</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> на научните статии не трябва да надвишават 20</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">стр., вкл. резюме на езика на статията, илюстративен материал, таблици и цитирана литература. Обзорите не трябва да надвишават 30 страници, а научните съобщения – 8 страници. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Ако </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">надвишаването на дадения обем е неизбежно, авторите трябва да имат готовност да платят такса, определена от редакцията. Ръкописите се представят в един отпечатан екземпляр или като файл в pdf-формат, по 30 реда на страница, 60-65 знака на ред. След като бъде приета за печат, статията се представя и в електронен вид в </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">MS</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">W</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">ord.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">doc</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">-формат, съдържащ текста, без сричкопренасяне.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Статиите се оформят и форматират по следните исиквания:</span></u></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•&#160;Font</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> –</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> Times New Roman, Size 14;</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•&#160;Page Setup</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> –</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> Top 2.0 cm, Bottom 2.0 cm, Left 2.5 cm, Right 2.5 cm;</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•&#160;Paper Size</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> –</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> A4, Line Spacing 1.5 lines, First Line by 1 cm;</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Заглавие </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">–</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> с главни букви, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Center</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Bold</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">;</span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Оставят се празни редове между следващите части;</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Имена на авторите – собствено и фамилно, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">center</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">bold</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, поставят се поредни номера на авторите (след името в </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Superscript</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">), когато са от различни институции;</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Институции на авторите, заедно с точните им адреси – </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">center</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, представят се на отделен ред, от частното към общото, със съответните номера отпред в </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Superscript</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">; авторът за кореспонденция посочва също </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">e</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">-</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">mail</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">адрес и факс.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Резюме (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Abstract</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">) – в един параграф до 20 реда, представящ проблема и/или целта, обектите и методите на изследване, по-важните резултати и завършващ с основното заключение (приноси). Избягвайте цитирания.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Ключови думи (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Key</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">words</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">) – ляво подравняване, до 6 броя и при възможност да не са част от заглавието.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Текст на ръкописа – препоръчва се утвърдената структура: Въведение (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Introduction</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Обект/Материал и методи на изследване (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Material</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">and</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Methods</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, Резултати и обсъждане (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Results</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">and</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Discussion</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, Заключение (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Conclusions</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Благодарности и </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Литература (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">References</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">)</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. Тези рубрики и евентуалните подзаглавия да са в </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">bold</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, ляво подравнени на отделен ред. Да се използват стандартни съкращения. Неспецифичните и нестандартни съкращения се изписват в скоби след термина при първото му появяване в текста. Мерните единици да следват системата </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">SI</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Използвайте</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">m</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">s</span><sup><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">-1</span></sup><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">вместо</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">m</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">/</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">s</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. Бинарните латински названия се използват в съответствие с международните номенклатурни правила. В заглавието и при първото споменаване в текста, след латинското име на видовете, да се включи името на автора. Латинските наименования на таксоните под ранг семейство се изписват в </span><em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Italic</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Таблиците – да имат номерация и наименование над тях, центрирано, съдържанието в таблиците да е </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">single</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">line</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">spacing</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Size</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> 10;</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Илюстрациите – черно-бели, да са изработени с някои от разпространените програмни продукти, да са интегрирани с текста и да имат номерация и наименование – под тях,; сканираните образи – в </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">TIF</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> или </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">JPEG</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> формат и минимум 200</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&#160;dpi</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. Публикуване на цветни илюстрации може да стане след заплащане от страна на авторите, определено от редакцията.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Цитиране на литературни източници – литературните източници се цитират с имената на авторите. Ако авторите са повече от двама, тогава се изписва сам</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">o</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> името на първия автор и след него се посочва „и др.“ (ако публикацията е на български), или „</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">et</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">al</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.“</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> (ако публикацията е на английски).</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Например: “Проучванията на Иванов и др. (2005) доказват, че...”, или “Това е потвърдено многократно от различни автори (Иванов и др. 2005, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Jones</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">et</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">al</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. 2006).”</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Библиография (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">References</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">) – включват се само цитираните литературни източници, подредени съгласно стандарта, по азбучен ред, без номериране. Ако статията е на български език, източниците на кирилица се подреждат преди тези на латиница, а ако статията е на английски език, заглавията на българските източници се превеждат на английски и след тях се записва в скоби (</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">in</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Bulgarian</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">). По същия начин се записват източнците, които са на друг, по-малко популярен език.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Примери: </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">- Статия в научно списание: </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Tashev</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">N</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">., </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Tsavkov</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">E</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">I</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">., 2008. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Medicinal</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">plants</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">of</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">the</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Bulgarian</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">dendroflora</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Phytologia</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Balcanica</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, 14(2): 269-278.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">- Статия в сборник от конференция, или глава от книга:</span></span></p><p style=\"text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">Kowarik I.<strong>, </strong>1995. Time lags in biological invasions with</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">regard to the success and failure of alien species. In</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">: </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">Pysek, P., Prach, K., Rejmánek, M.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">,</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\"> Wade, M.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">(eds,) </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">Plant invasions: general aspects and special</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">problems</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\"> SPB Academic Publishing, Amsterdam</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">: </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32); font-size: 10pt;\">15–38.</span><span style=\"color: black; font-size: 10pt;\"> </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">- Дисертация:</span></span></p><p style=\"text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Gray M.C., 2007. An investigation into the role of genetics in the tolerance of Texas live oaks to <em>Ceratocystis fagacearum</em>. Ph</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">D</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">thesis</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Texas</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&amp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">M</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">University</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">, 149 </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">pp</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span> </span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">- Книга:</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Sokal</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">R</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">., </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Rohlf</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">F</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">J</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">., 1996. </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Biometry, Third edition, W.H.Freeman, 880 pp. </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Източници на други, по-малко популярни езици: </span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Jansons Ā., 2008. Theoretical basis and perspectives of Scots pine (<em>Pinus sylvestris</em> L.) in Latvia. Ph.D. thesis, Jelgava, LLU, 110 pp. (in Latvian)</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">&#160;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Страниците да се номерират.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">&#160;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Допълнителни условия:</span></u></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Таблиците и</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">фигурите да се представят и на отделна страница,</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">оригиналният файл (например в </span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Excel</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">) да е записан отделно.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Да се приложат имената,</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> научните звания и степени</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> на авторите, точното наименование на институцията, в която работят, служебен адрес, телефон и E-mail.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•&#160;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Статиите ще бъдат рецензирани от компетентни рецензенти</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">. Становището и бележките на рецензента се предоставят на автора за кореспонденция в срок до 2 месеца.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•&#160;Статиите в окончателен вид, в pdf-формат и в MS Word.doc формат, трябва да се изпращат обратно до редакцията не по-късно от 1 месец след получаване на становището и бележките на рецензента.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Статиите се публикуват по реда на постъпване и одобряване.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Ръкописи не се връщат.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">&#160;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Допълнителни изисквания към статиите на български език:</span></u></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Представят се резюме и ключови думи и на английски език.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">•</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Заглавията над таблиците, текстовете под фигурите и всички български текстове в таблиците и фигурите да се представят и на английски език.</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\">&#160;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Материалите да се изпращат на следния адрес:</span></u></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 17.85pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">1756, София</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 17.85pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Бул. „Климент Охридски” №</span>&#160;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">10</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 17.85pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Лесотехнически университет</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 17.85pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Списание „Лесовъдска мисъл”</span></span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-left: 17.85pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">E</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">-</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">mail</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">: </span></span><span style=\"font-family: Tahoma;\"><a href=\"mailto:Lesmis@ltu.bg\"><u><font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; text-decoration: none;\">Lesmis</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; text-decoration: none;\">@</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; text-decoration: none;\">ltu</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; text-decoration: none;\">.</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; text-decoration: none;\">bg</span></font></u></a><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"> </span></span></p>', '<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; The following types of publications are acceptable: regular paper, review, brief communication and announcements for conferences and symposia. The languages of the journal are English and Bulgarian.<span style=\"background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% yellow;\"> </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp; The manuscripts of the regular papers should not exceed 20 pages, including an Abstract in the language of the paper, illustrations, tables and references. The reviews should not exceed 30 pages, and the brief communications – 8 pages. If exceeding of the maximum allowed volume is unavoidable, the authors must be ready to pay a charge determined by the Editorial office. The manuscripts must be submitted in one hard copy or in pdf-format, with 30 rows per page, 60-65 characters per row. After accepting the paper for publication, the authors must submit it in MS Word.doc-format, containing the text, without hyphenation. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><u>The papers must be formatted according to the following rules:</u></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Font – Times New Roman, Size 14;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Page Setup – Top 2.0 cm, Bottom 2.0 cm, Left 2.5 cm, Right 2.5 cm;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Paper Size – A4, Line Spacing 1.5 lines, First Line by 1 cm;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Title – Capital letters, Centered, Bold;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Please, leave blank lines between the following parts;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Author name(s) – centered, bold, numbered in Superscript after the names (in a case when the authors have different affiliations);</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Authors’ affiliations - addresses – centered, presented on a separate row, with the respective numbers in Superscript at the beginning; the corresponding author should provide an e-mail and fax No. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Abstract – one paragraph up to 20 rows, presenting the problem and/or the objectives, more important results and the main inference and contributions. Avoid citing references. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 9pt 2pt 0cm; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Key words – up to 6, and if possible, not repeating words from the title. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Text – the traditional structure is recommended: Introduction, Material and Methods, Results, Discussion (the last two could be merged), Conclusions, Acknowledgments and References. These parts and the sub-titles must be in bold, left-lined, on separate rows. Standard abbreviations must be used. The non-specific abbreviation should be given in brackets after the first mentioning of the respective term. SI-system units must be used. Use m.s<sup>-1</sup> instead m/s. Standard binomial nomenclature should be used for the scientific names of the taxa. When a given nomen appear first in the text, the authors name should be given as well. The Latin names below the family rank must be italicized. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;The tables must be numbered according to their appearance in the text. They should have titles above; the content must be centered, single line spacing, Size 10.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Black and white figures must be done using some of the most popular software packages. They should be integrated with the text, numbered and with centered text below. The scanned images must be saved in TIF or JPEG format, at minimum 200&nbsp;dpi. Printing of colour figures could be done after additional payment by the authors depending on the figure size.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Citing references – the references must be cited with the authors names. When the authors are more than two, then the name of the first author is written followed by “et al.” For example, “The studies of Ivanov et al. (2005) showed that…”, or “This was confirmed by many authors (Ivanov et al. 2005, Jones et al. 2006)”.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;References – only the references cited in the text should be included here. They must be arranged in alphabetical order, without numbering. The references in other, less popular languages, must be translated into English and at the end the original language must be indicated in brackets.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Examples:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Paper in a journal: </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Tashev A.N., Tsavkov E.I., 2008. Medicinal plants of the Bulgarian dendroflora. Phytologia Balcanica, 14(2): 269-278.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Paper in a conference proceedings, or chapter in a book:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">Kowarik I.<strong>, </strong>1995. Time lags in biological invasions with<span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\"> </span>regard to the success and failure of alien species. In</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">: </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">Pysek, P., Prach, K., Rejmánek, M.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">,</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\"> Wade, M.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">(eds,) </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">Plant invasions: general aspects and special</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\"> </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">problems</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">.</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\"> SPB Academic Publishing, Amsterdam</span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">: </span><span style=\"color: rgb(35, 31, 32);\">15–38.</span><span style=\"color: black;\"> </span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Ph.D. thesis:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: -36pt; margin-left: 36pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Gray M.C., 2007. An investigation into the role of genetics in the tolerance of Texas live oaks to <em>Ceratocystis fagacearum</em>. Ph.D. thesis, Texas A&amp;M University, 149 pp. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- Book:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Sokal R., Rohlf F.J., 1996. Biometry, Third edition, W.H.Freeman, 880 pp. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">- References published in less popular languages:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Jansons Ā., 2008. Theoretical basis and perspectives of Scots pine (<em>Pinus sylvestris</em> L.) in Latvia. Ph.D. thesis, Jelgava, LLU, 110 pp. (in Latvian) </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;The pages should be numbered. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><u>Additional requirements:</u></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;The tables and figures must be submitted in separate sheets, and the original files (for example, in Excel format) must be presented separately.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;The names, titles and degrees of the authors are desirable, together with the name of the respective institutions, address, phone and e-mail.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Each manuscript will be reviewed by an independent reviewer. The opinion and the remarks of the reviewer will be provided to the author for correspondence within two months.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;The final versions of the papers, in pdf-format and in MS Word.doc format should be sent to the Editorial office within a month after receiving the opinion and remarks of the reviewer.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;The papers will be published according to their order of acceptance.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 2pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;No manuscripts will be returned to authors. </span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><u>The submissions should be sent to:</u></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><u>Editor-in-Chief</u></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 6pt;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><u>Forestry Ideas</u></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">University of Forestry </span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">10, Kliment Ohridski Blvd. </span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">1756, Sofia, Bulgaria</span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 11px;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">E-mail: <span style=\"color: blue;\"><a href=\"mailto:Lesmis@ltu.bg\"><u><font color=\"#000000\"><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">Lesmis</span><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">@</span><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">ltu</span><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">.</span><span style=\"text-decoration: none;\">bg</span></font></u></a></span> </span></span></p>\r\n');
INSERT INTO `instr_to_autors` (`instrID`, `instrText`) VALUES
(1, '<p>\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, sans-serif; text-align: justify;\">The following types of publications are acceptable: regular paper, review, brief communication and announcements for conferences and symposia. The language of the journal is English.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">The manuscripts of the regular papers should not exceed 15 printed pages, including an abstract, tables, figures, illustrations, and references. The reviews should not exceed 30 pages, and the brief communications – 8 pages. The manuscripts must be submitted in pdf-format and in MS Word.doc-format, containing the text, without hyphenation.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><u><span style=\"line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Publication fee (from 01.01.2020):</span></u></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"color:#333333;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\">If a submission is accepted for publication, author will be asked to pay the article publication fee to cover publication costs (it covers organizing a review process, English language correction, prepress, and publication on website). The fee is </span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"color:#333333;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\">10€ per page. </span></span></span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><span style=\"color:#333333;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\">If exceeding of the maximum allowed volume is unavoidable, the authors must be ready to pay a charge at 15€ per each additional page (after approval by the editor).</span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 6pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<u><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">The papers must be formatted according to the following rules:</span></span></u></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, sans-serif;\">•&nbsp;Font – Times New Roman, Size 12.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Page Setup – Top 2.5 cm, Bottom 2.5 cm, Left 2.5 cm, Right 2.5 cm.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Paper Size – A4, Line spacing 1.5 lines, First line by 1 cm.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Title – Capital letters, Centered, Bold.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Author(s) name(s) – centered, numbered in superscript after the names (in a case when the authors have different affiliations) and the corresponding author should be marked with an asterisk (*).</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Authors’ affiliations – address(es): department(s), institution(s), location(s), post code, country, e-mail – centered; presented on a separate row, with the respective numbers in superscript at the beginning; English letters only, size 11.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Abstract – one paragraph up to 300 words, presenting the problem and/or the objectives, more important results and the main inference and contributions. Avoid citing references.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Key words – up to 6 (except the words found in the title).</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Text – the traditional structure is recommended: Introduction, Material and Methods, Results, Discussion (the last two could be merged), Conclusions, Acknowledgments (if applicable) and References. These sub-titles must be in bold, left-lined, on separate rows. Prospective their subheadings are in bold and on a separate line.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Standard abbreviations must be used (e.g., i.e., et al., a.s.l., DNA, etc., and other). The non-specific abbreviation should be given in brackets after the first mentioning of the respective term. International System of Units (SI) should be used. It is recommended to use m·s<sup>-1</sup> instead m/s. Standard binomial nomenclature should be used for the scientific names of the taxa. When a given nomen appear first in the text, the author\'s name should be given as well. The latin names below the family rank must be italicized.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Tables – must be numbered in Arabic numerals according to their appearance in the text. They should have titles above, centered, bold, size 11. The table should be built without vertical and with minimum horizontal lines. The content must be centered, single line spacing, size 10. The abbreviations used in tables should be defined in a note below, size 11.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Illustrations (graphs, photographs, drawings, maps etc.) must be numbered as figures in Arabic numerals according to their appearance in the text. They can be black and white or in color. The titles should be below, centered, bold, size 11. Photographs and drawings should be of high contrast and sharp.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Tables and figures should be referred to in the text. They should be submitted in separate original files, such as Excel, JPEG or TIFF format. The scanned images must be saved at minimum 300&nbsp;dpi. The same data should not be duplicated in both tables and figures. The abbreviations in the tables and figures should be defined in the note below, size 11.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;Citing references – the references must be cited with the author’s names as follows: (Jonson 2010), (Jonson and Spiecker 2010), (Jonson et al. 2010). When the authors are more than two, then the name of the first author is written followed by \'et al.\'. For example, \'The studies of Ivanov et al. (2005) showed that…\', or \'This was confirmed by other authors (Ivanov et al. 2005, Jones et al. 2006)\', or \'Our results corroborated these established by other authors (Dimitrov 2010, Popov et al. 2009, Spiecker et al. 2008)\'. In such cases the sources are presented in the order they are presented in the Bibliography. Citing sources that have no author should be cited by first word of the title, ellipsis and year, or as \'Anonymous\' and year. For examples: (Alabama ... 2007) or (Anonymous 2006) (see the examples below).</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">•&nbsp;References – only the references cited in the text should be included here. They must be arranged in alphabetical order (Harvard system), without numbering, size 11. The references in other, less popular languages, must be translated into English. Sources by the same author(s) and in the same year should be listed as 2014a, 2014b, etc. Use of DOI is encouraged. Examples of citation:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">- Paper in a journal:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt 1cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Tashev&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">A., Tsavkov E.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">2008. Medicinal plants of the Bulgarian dendroflora. Phytologia Balcanica 14(2): 269–278.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 3pt 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">- Paper in a conference proceedings, or chapter in a book:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt 1cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Kowarik&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">I</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">.1995. Time lags in biological invasions with regard to the success and failure of alien species. In: Pysek P., Prach K., Rejmánek M., Wade M. (Eds). Plant invasions: general aspects and special problems. SPB Academic Publishing, Amsterdam: 15–38.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 3pt 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">- PhD thesis:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt 1cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Gray&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">M.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">2007. An investigation into the role of genetics in the tolerance of Texas live oaks to <em>Ceratocystis fagacearum</em></span>. PhD thesis. Texas A&amp;M University. 149 p.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 3pt 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">- Book:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt 1cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Sokal&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">R., Rohlf F.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">1996. Biometry. Third edition, Freeman W.H. 880 p.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 3pt 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">- References published in less popular languages:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt 1cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<strong><span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-caps: small-caps; font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Jansons&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">Ā. 2008. Theoretical basis and perspectives of Scots pine (<em>Pinus sylvestris</em></span> L.) in Latvia. [Parastās priedes (<em>Pinus sylvestris</em></span> L.) selekcijas teorētiskie pamati un attīstības perspektīvas Latvijā]. PhD thesis. Jelgava, LLU. 110 p. (in Latvian).</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 3pt 9.05pt 3pt 0cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">\r\n	<span style=\"font-family:arial,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\">- Sources without author:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 3pt 1cm; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: